cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a deep learning approach for boundary detection in medical images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a 3D CNN architecture and multi-scale feature learning suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the approach on a dataset of medical images suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of deep learning techniques suggests a potential fit for neural networks (cs.NE).
